The family guarded that manuscript with great fervor.

01:09:22.360 --> 01:09:32.400
And the other question, and you'd have to go back and look at the, when did the translations

01:09:32.400 --> 01:09:38.640
of Jung start appearing in French, for example, because not everybody spoke and read all of

01:09:38.640 --> 01:09:41.400
the European languages.

01:09:41.400 --> 01:09:49.680
And I don't think that Freud, I don't think, excuse me, that Jung starts appearing in translation

01:09:49.680 --> 01:09:56.520
until maybe the late 20s, which would be, you know, the horse was already out of the

01:09:56.520 --> 01:09:58.000
chute in terms of Freud.

01:09:58.000 --> 01:09:59.760
But Freud was not that much earlier.

01:09:59.760 --> 01:10:03.520
Freud only started in 1920, the first French translations and then continued on through

01:10:03.520 --> 01:10:04.520
the 20s.

01:10:04.520 --> 01:10:05.520
But he had the grip on the men.

01:10:05.520 --> 01:10:06.520
He had the grip on the men.

01:10:06.520 --> 01:10:10.080
I didn't read this other guy, you know.

01:10:10.080 --> 01:10:17.320
But in many ways, Jung is, in many ways more appropriate to surrealism.

01:10:17.320 --> 01:10:20.760
And Freud is.

01:10:20.760 --> 01:10:21.760
Yeah.

01:10:21.760 --> 01:10:22.760
Yeah.

01:10:22.760 --> 01:10:23.760
Are you almost sort of wise?

01:10:23.760 --> 01:10:24.760
Yeah.

01:10:24.760 --> 01:10:25.760
I agree with you.

01:10:25.760 --> 01:10:26.760
Yeah.

