No, the relationship with the painters between the painters and the poets was, historically,

01:17:43.680 --> 01:17:51.320
it's actually rather interesting and rather difficult one because, as Henry pointed out,

01:17:51.320 --> 01:17:56.880
at first there was a kind of a, Breton had actually initially begun by saying that there

01:17:56.880 --> 01:18:02.640
could be no such thing as surrealist painting and sort of had eliminated the idea of a visual

01:18:02.640 --> 01:18:10.480
surrealism at the very beginning of the movement and was partly pushed into having to then make

01:18:10.480 --> 01:18:14.360
a theoretical statement, which of course became surrealism and painting, a book that he started

01:18:14.360 --> 01:18:19.920
in 1928 as an essay and eventually was added to throughout the rest of his life.

01:18:19.920 --> 01:18:26.800
A major statement about what visual surrealism is, but oddly enough, it was sort of arm-twisted

01:18:26.800 --> 01:18:36.920
a little bit into making that statement because one of the other members of the group had

